  "lesson": {
    "title": "Fast vs Slow RC Timing",
    "description": "Flip the slide switch on. Shared 470Ω feeds a cross: west branch has 100µF + red LED (fast τ), east branch has 1000µF + red LED (slow τ). Watch both when you switch on or off — the small cap’s LED responds quickly, the big cap’s LED fades slowly. Same resistor, different C. LEDs at 90°; cap + toward power on each branch."
